00:06:06.022 --> 00:06:07.060
Closing Thoughts

00:06:08.560 --> 00:06:11.197
I had a lot of fun with this project.

00:06:11.697 --> 00:06:21.767
It really ended up combining a bunch of my interests, including hardware hacking, software (both on an embedded device and server), and utilizing some state of the art AI models too!

00:06:22.267 --> 00:06:26.902
I also got to 3D print a case that’s much more complicated than anything else I’ve made myself.

00:06:27.902 --> 00:06:38.051
It was fun coming up with this challenge and then solving all of the problems that came with it, including fitting everything in the case, and lining up all of the components like the screen and buttons.

00:06:39.051 --> 00:06:45.365
While I think it would be really interesting to see this device hit the mainstream market, I don’t think it will happen any time soon.

00:06:45.865 --> 00:06:49.301
For one thing, the licensing of real voices would probably be an issue.

00:06:49.801 --> 00:06:54.835
Plus the hardware to run the inference on a device doesn’t exist as far as I know.

00:06:55.335 --> 00:07:02.368
I think you might be able to do it on an iPhone if you shrank the model, but that wouldn’t be nearly as fun as using a dedicated device.

00:07:03.368 --> 00:07:11.359
I’m hoping that I’m wrong though, and that a 30th anniversary Talkboy makes its way to the toy stores, complete with the latest in AI tech!
